 So if I'm repenting, if I'm walking this way,

259
00:10:09,200 --> 00:10:12,000
 to repent would mean to turn around, right?

260
00:10:12,000 --> 00:10:13,880
 So that's what this young man is doing.

261
00:10:13,880 --> 00:10:16,760
 He is turning around in his mind and his perspective,

262
00:10:16,760 --> 00:10:19,120
 but then he also physically turns around.

263
00:10:19,120 --> 00:10:21,360
 He returns to the Father.

264
00:10:21,360 --> 00:10:25,660
 He leaves his foolish thinking and his foolish living,

265
00:10:25,660 --> 00:10:29,040
 and he makes his way back to the Father.

266
00:10:30,160 --> 00:10:33,800
 And what Jesus partially tells us this story

267
00:10:33,800 --> 00:10:35,240
 so that we can get to this next part

268
00:10:35,240 --> 00:10:36,460
 about what happens next,

269
00:10:36,460 --> 00:10:38,320
 when we would turn and we would repent,

270
00:10:38,320 --> 00:10:40,540
 which is actually the reason I was so excited

271
00:10:40,540 --> 00:10:42,360
 about preaching this specific sermon

272
00:10:42,360 --> 00:10:44,200
 is for this next section.

273
00:10:44,200 --> 00:10:48,560
 The son that repents and turns, what happens to him next?

274
00:10:48,560 --> 00:10:52,960
 The story goes that, well, the Father does something crazy,

275
00:10:52,960 --> 00:10:55,960
 does something radical, something that is off script

276
00:10:55,960 --> 00:10:57,480
 that no one would expect, right?

277
00:10:57,480 --> 00:10:59,560
 The Father isn't reckless.

278
00:10:59,560 --> 00:11:03,800
 The Father is responding to deep love.

279
00:11:03,800 --> 00:11:05,400
 The Father is calculated.

280
00:11:05,400 --> 00:11:06,760
 The actions of the Father

281
00:11:06,760 --> 00:11:09,960
 are therefore interested in restoring.

282
00:11:09,960 --> 00:11:10,800
 The text would say this,

283
00:11:10,800 --> 00:11:13,240
 while he was a long way off, speaking of the son,

284
00:11:13,240 --> 00:11:16,780
 his father saw him and was filled with compassion.

285
00:11:16,780 --> 00:11:20,880
 He ran to his son, threw his arms around him and kissed him.

286
00:11:20,880 --> 00:11:22,760
 The son said, "Father, I've sinned against heaven

287
00:11:22,760 --> 00:11:23,600
 "and against you.

288
00:11:23,600 --> 00:11:27,080
 "I'm no longer worthy to be called your son."

289
00:11:27,080 --> 00:11:28,180
 But the father said to his servants,

290
00:11:28,180 --> 00:11:31,400
 "Quick, bring the best robe, put it on him.

291
00:11:31,400 --> 00:11:33,580
 "Put a ring on his finger and sandals on his feet.

292
00:11:33,580 --> 00:11:36,040
 "Bring the fattened calf and kill it.

293
00:11:36,040 --> 00:11:37,520
 "Let's have a feast and celebrate,

294
00:11:37,520 --> 00:11:39,680
 "for the son of mine was dead and is alive again.

295
00:11:39,680 --> 00:11:42,200
 "He was lost and is now found."

296
00:11:42,200 --> 00:11:44,400
 So they began to celebrate.

297
00:11:44,400 --> 00:11:47,640
 The father is overjoyed to see the son again.

298
00:11:47,640 --> 00:11:50,200
 He doesn't wait for the son to make it all the way back.

299
00:11:50,200 --> 00:11:52,400
 He says, while he was a long way off,

300
00:11:52,400 --> 00:11:54,360
 the father sprints toward him.

301
00:11:54,360 --> 00:11:56,120
 The son's not even close to being home yet.

302
00:11:56,120 --> 00:11:57,720
 The father doesn't even meet him halfway.

303
00:11:57,720 --> 00:11:59,740
 This idea that God's gonna meet us halfway

304
00:11:59,740 --> 00:12:01,580
 is not biblical, right?

305
00:12:01,580 --> 00:12:02,840
 Like God goes the whole way.

306
00:12:02,840 --> 00:12:04,800
 Like the son is all the way over there

307
00:12:04,800 --> 00:12:06,640
 and the father sees that he's turned around

308
00:12:06,640 --> 00:12:09,040
 and is coming back and he runs towards him

309
00:12:09,040 --> 00:12:13,880
 in compassion, overjoyed about this.

310
00:12:13,880 --> 00:12:16,200
 And I think it gets me, what gets me is

311
00:12:16,200 --> 00:12:18,240
 when I try to visualize how beautiful this is.

312
00:12:18,240 --> 00:12:20,600
 I think about my three-year-old son

313
00:12:20,600 --> 00:12:23,200
 and how if there was a moment where he's coming to me,

314
00:12:23,200 --> 00:12:25,320
 we used to live in Chonquano

315
00:12:25,320 --> 00:12:26,980
 and I used to get home from work late

316
00:12:26,980 --> 00:12:28,920
 and it'd be around maybe like seven or something

317
00:12:28,920 --> 00:12:30,840
 and my wife would leave our estate

318
00:12:30,840 --> 00:12:33,240
 and start walking towards us and I'd be walking home.

319
00:12:33,240 --> 00:12:35,100
 And the second I saw my son,

320
00:12:35,100 --> 00:12:37,280
 I mean, I didn't physically run

321
00:12:37,280 --> 00:12:39,200
 because it's hot in Hong Kong, but my heart ran.

322
00:12:39,200 --> 00:12:41,880
 I was thrilled, I was so excited.

323
00:12:41,880 --> 00:12:43,040
 I could only imagine, you know,

324
00:12:43,040 --> 00:12:45,360
 when I've not seen my son for a whole day,

325
00:12:45,360 --> 00:12:47,080
 this dude's son has been in a different country.

326
00:12:47,080 --> 00:12:50,640
 The condition and the appearance of the son is saddening,

327
00:12:50,640 --> 00:12:52,480
 probably breaks his heart.

328
00:12:52,480 --> 00:12:55,680
 So it probably pushes him even more into that moment.

329
00:12:55,680 --> 00:12:58,660
 But the father runs to him, drops everything

330
00:12:58,660 --> 00:13:02,620
 and is filled with compassion to see his boy again.

331
00:13:02,620 --> 00:13:09,780
 This is a decisive and aggressive, fervent love.

332
00:13:09,780 --> 00:13:11,660
 It's extreme grace.

333
00:13:11,660 --> 00:13:13,180
 And it's extreme grace because note this,

334
00:13:13,180 --> 00:13:15,300
 the father could have just forgiven him.

335
00:13:15,300 --> 00:13:17,620
 This would have been a beautiful parable

336
00:13:17,620 --> 00:13:20,140
 if it was about how a son really messed up.

337
00:13:20,140 --> 00:13:23,080
 I mean, as bad as it gets and he gets what he deserves.

338
00:13:23,080 --> 00:13:25,440
 And when he comes and tries to apologize,

339
00:13:25,440 --> 00:13:28,380
 the father says, "Okay, you're forgiven."

340
00:13:28,380 --> 00:13:29,260
 And that's the end of the parable.

341
00:13:29,260 --> 00:13:30,580
 If that was the story,

342
00:13:30,580 --> 00:13:33,020
 that would be a pretty powerful parable.

343
00:13:33,020 --> 00:13:36,220
 But it doesn't just stop there.

344
00:13:36,220 --> 00:13:39,180
 The father's love is so extreme.

345
00:13:39,180 --> 00:13:42,180
 It's so extreme that the son tries to get out his phrase,

346
00:13:42,180 --> 00:13:44,580
 "Father, I've sinned against heaven and against you.

347
00:13:44,580 --> 00:13:45,500
 I'm no longer worried."

348
00:13:45,500 --> 00:13:47,140
 And I imagine the father just putting his hand

349
00:13:47,140 --> 00:13:51,320
 to his son's mouth, saying, "Stop, you're my son.

350
00:13:51,320 --> 00:13:55,260
 You're here, that's what matters."

351
00:13:55,260 --> 00:13:58,100
 And the father doesn't just forgive him.

352
00:13:58,100 --> 00:13:59,900
 The father reinstates him.

353
00:13:59,900 --> 00:14:01,740
 Rather than saying, "All is forgiven.

354
00:14:01,740 --> 00:14:03,380
 Your slate is clean."

355
00:14:03,380 --> 00:14:06,700
 The father says, "Go get the best stuff we have.

356
00:14:06,700 --> 00:14:09,420
 Get the best robe," he says.

357
00:14:09,420 --> 00:14:13,100
 "Get a ring, get a sandal, kill the A5 Wagyu."

358
00:14:13,100 --> 00:14:16,660
 Like he wants the good stuff for his son

359
00:14:16,660 --> 00:14:19,180
 who has just done all this mess.

360
00:14:19,180 --> 00:14:22,640
 He does not just forgive us, he reinstates.

361
00:14:23,900 --> 00:14:26,140
 And I think we have to come to the understanding

362
00:14:26,140 --> 00:14:27,780
 that this is God's posture.

363
00:14:27,780 --> 00:14:31,280
 This is the father's posture to us as well.

364
00:14:31,280 --> 00:14:34,560
 Can we talk about how,

365
00:14:34,560 --> 00:14:38,340
 if I put myself in the position of the son,

366
00:14:38,340 --> 00:14:40,100
 forgiveness would have been great.

367
00:14:40,100 --> 00:14:43,100
 But I wonder how he felt when his dad hugged him

368
00:14:43,100 --> 00:14:44,420
 in that moment.

369
00:14:44,420 --> 00:14:46,740
 I wonder what he felt when he's dirty and stinky

370
00:14:46,740 --> 00:14:50,860
 and smelly and tired and exhausted and not worthy,

371
00:14:50,860 --> 00:14:53,860
 yet his father throws his arms around him.

372
00:14:53,860 --> 00:14:56,780
 Talk about getting more than you deserve.

373
00:14:56,780 --> 00:14:58,060
 I feel like that motion probably,

374
00:14:58,060 --> 00:15:03,060
 that moment probably flooded him with plenty of emotion

375
00:15:03,060 --> 00:15:05,800
 to be received again.

376
00:15:05,800 --> 00:15:09,680
 See, the father had no intention

377
00:15:09,680 --> 00:15:11,780
 of making a repentant son a slave.

378
00:15:11,780 --> 00:15:12,980
 And I think we have to hear that

379
00:15:12,980 --> 00:15:14,140
 for what it's really saying.

380
00:15:14,140 --> 00:15:16,760
 Our father has no intention

381
00:15:16,760 --> 00:15:19,260
 of making a repentant us a slave,

382
00:15:19,260 --> 00:15:22,020
 but rather in his great joy,

383
00:15:22,020 --> 00:15:25,500
 he restores us back to sonship and daughtership.

384
00:15:25,500 --> 00:15:27,020
 It is joy that he does it.

385
00:15:27,020 --> 00:15:28,460
 It's not because he has to,

386
00:15:28,460 --> 00:15:30,540
 because he's God, because he's obligated.

387
00:15:30,540 --> 00:15:31,540
 It's within his joy.

388
00:15:31,540 --> 00:15:32,420
 If you don't believe me,

389
00:15:32,420 --> 00:15:33,780
 three different times it says it.

390
00:15:33,780 --> 00:15:35,620
 In the first parable about the sheep,

391
00:15:35,620 --> 00:15:37,820
 it says this, at the very end of it,

392
00:15:37,820 --> 00:15:40,480
 he goes, "Rejoice with me, I have found my lost sheep."

393
00:15:40,480 --> 00:15:42,900
 When the parable gets to the next part about the coin,

394
00:15:42,900 --> 00:15:45,480
 the woman says, "Rejoice with me, I have found my lost coin."

395
00:15:45,480 --> 00:15:47,060
 When it gets to the son for the third time,

396
00:15:47,060 --> 00:15:49,780
 "Rejoice and celebrate, be glad."

397
00:15:49,780 --> 00:15:53,520
 There is joy that God feels about restoring you.

398
00:15:53,520 --> 00:15:58,240
 When you come back, it is in his joy to bring you,

399
00:15:58,240 --> 00:16:01,860
 not just to forgive you, but to reinstate you,

400
00:16:01,860 --> 00:16:05,160
 to bring you into the family of God.

401
00:16:05,160 --> 00:16:06,480
 Because in that space,

402
00:16:06,480 --> 00:16:08,980
 there is a relationship that is restored.

403
00:16:08,980 --> 00:16:10,820
 In that space, there is hope,

404
00:16:10,820 --> 00:16:13,700
 there is meaning, there is identity.

405
00:16:13,700 --> 00:16:16,080
 He wants to provide all of that for us.

406
00:16:17,420 --> 00:16:19,340
 This restored identity is a theme

407
00:16:19,340 --> 00:16:21,980
 that we cannot afford to overlook.

408
00:16:21,980 --> 00:16:24,540
 There's something to be said about how identity

409
00:16:24,540 --> 00:16:28,660
 and relationship are major threads into this story,

410
00:16:28,660 --> 00:16:31,580
 and into the kingdom of God as a whole.

411
00:16:31,580 --> 00:16:33,220
 I think that's why this story is drenched

412
00:16:33,220 --> 00:16:34,700
 with identity imagery.

413
00:16:34,700 --> 00:16:36,580
 Did you notice how every main character

414
00:16:36,580 --> 00:16:40,820
 isn't referred to by their name, or by their job?

415
00:16:40,820 --> 00:16:45,340
 It's the father, it's the son, it's the other son.

416
00:16:45,340 --> 00:16:48,700
 Right, like who they are communicated as

417
00:16:48,700 --> 00:16:51,080
 is based off of relationship.

418
00:16:51,080 --> 00:16:52,780
 Relationship is so important.

419
00:16:52,780 --> 00:16:55,260
 It elevates the meaning of this parable.

