00:18:54,620 --> 00:18:57,900
 There is something so significant

468
00:18:57,900 --> 00:19:01,100
 in this relationship identity concept

469
00:19:01,100 --> 00:19:02,540
 that the scripture wants us to understand

470
00:19:02,540 --> 00:19:03,700
 and it's because of this.

471
00:19:03,700 --> 00:19:07,700
 As children of God, we get certain perks.

472
00:19:07,700 --> 00:19:10,080
 There are things that happen within the family

473
00:19:10,080 --> 00:19:12,460
 that won't happen outside the family.

474
00:19:12,460 --> 00:19:14,220
 The way I love my son would be inappropriate

475
00:19:14,220 --> 00:19:17,060
 for me to love any other person that way.

476
00:19:17,060 --> 00:19:19,420
 The way I love my spouse or my daughter

477
00:19:19,420 --> 00:19:20,260
 would be very different

478
00:19:20,260 --> 00:19:21,780
 than the way I'm gonna love my friends

479
00:19:21,780 --> 00:19:23,300
 or the way I'm gonna engage with my friends.

480
00:19:23,300 --> 00:19:25,620
 See, when you're in the family, there's something different.

481
00:19:25,620 --> 00:19:27,380
 There's a grace that's for the family,

482
00:19:27,380 --> 00:19:29,380
 there's a certain compassion that's for the family.

483
00:19:29,380 --> 00:19:32,100
 The family deeply matters.

