00:31:38,360 --> 00:31:41,440
 Our proximity to Christ isn't a badge we wear

777
00:31:41,440 --> 00:31:43,400
 that makes us better than other people.

778
00:31:43,400 --> 00:31:47,720
 It's not.

779
00:31:47,720 --> 00:31:50,800
 It's not our permission to point and say,

780
00:31:50,800 --> 00:31:52,620
 look how bad they're doing.

781
00:31:52,620 --> 00:31:56,320
 Doesn't give us a right to get online

782
00:31:56,320 --> 00:31:57,860
 and blast everyone that's not a Christian

783
00:31:57,860 --> 00:31:59,640
 for the ridiculous things that they might do.

784
00:31:59,640 --> 00:32:00,480
 Guess what?

785
00:32:00,480 --> 00:32:01,400
 They're not Christians.

786
00:32:01,400 --> 00:32:02,240
 Imagine that.

787
00:32:04,160 --> 00:32:08,240
 No, our proximity to God is meant to draw us close to him

788
00:32:08,240 --> 00:32:10,360
 so that we can be transformed by him.

789
00:32:10,360 --> 00:32:14,000
 Being close to God is less about being holier than others.

790
00:32:14,000 --> 00:32:17,240
 It's more about becoming like him,

791
00:32:17,240 --> 00:32:19,920
 becoming extreme in our grace,

792
00:32:19,920 --> 00:32:24,400
 choosing compassion over judgment,

793
00:32:24,400 --> 00:32:26,800
 oozing with compassion when our brothers and sisters

794
00:32:26,800 --> 00:32:30,000
 are lost, being excited to see them come home,

795
00:32:30,000 --> 00:32:32,620
 co-laboring with the Father.

796
00:32:32,620 --> 00:32:34,800
 That's my heart for me, my family.

797
00:32:34,800 --> 00:32:36,840
 That's my heart for us as a community.

798
00:32:36,840 --> 00:32:38,600
 That in our weekly gatherings,

799
00:32:38,600 --> 00:32:41,560
 in the gatherings that take place outside of Sundays here,

800
00:32:41,560 --> 00:32:44,480
 that we would be growing in our likeness of God.

801
00:32:44,480 --> 00:32:46,800
 That our hearts would be becoming softer

802
00:32:46,800 --> 00:32:48,280
 and being more like his.

803
00:32:48,280 --> 00:32:50,000
 That he would replace the heart of stone

804
00:32:50,000 --> 00:32:51,040
 and give us a heart of flesh.

805
00:32:51,040 --> 00:32:53,280
 That he would wipe away the scales from our eyes

806
00:32:53,280 --> 00:32:56,500
 and we would see people the way that he sees them,

807
00:32:56,500 --> 00:32:58,000
 being shaped like him.

808
00:32:58,000 --> 00:33:00,280
 That we would be broken for the lost

809
00:33:00,280 --> 00:33:02,200
 the way that he's broken for the lost.

810
00:33:02,200 --> 00:33:05,080
 That we would rejoice when they come home.

811
00:33:05,080 --> 00:33:08,760
 We would rejoice when they repent.

812
00:33:08,760 --> 00:33:11,880
 And for me, where I find this most challenging,

813
00:33:11,880 --> 00:33:13,320
 I have to ask myself this,

814
00:33:13,320 --> 00:33:18,320
 would I be rejoicing, celebrating,

815
00:33:18,320 --> 00:33:20,520
 in the worst person that I know,

816
00:33:20,520 --> 00:33:22,320
 most filthy person that I know,

817
00:33:22,320 --> 00:33:23,540
 the liar, the cheater,

818
00:33:23,540 --> 00:33:25,760
 the one who's weaseled their way,

819
00:33:25,760 --> 00:33:26,880
 who's offended me,

820
00:33:26,880 --> 00:33:30,160
 comes into God's family,

821
00:33:30,160 --> 00:33:32,460
 and he gets the exact same privilege as I do.

822
00:33:32,460 --> 00:33:34,600
 Can I celebrate at that?

823
00:33:34,600 --> 00:33:38,680
 Because I think it's that what drives the son crazy,

824
00:33:38,680 --> 00:33:40,160
 it's not just that he's forgiven,

825
00:33:40,160 --> 00:33:43,200
 it's that he's now restored to the same level.

826
00:33:43,200 --> 00:33:44,840
 And that blood of Jesus, like Emma said,

827
00:33:44,840 --> 00:33:46,920
 that is our ultimate equalizer.

828
00:33:46,920 --> 00:33:49,320
 That's what makes us all be able to be

829
00:33:49,320 --> 00:33:51,040
 on the same level again.

830
00:33:51,040 --> 00:33:53,280
 And that's what the father is ultimately showing us

831
00:33:53,280 --> 00:33:54,280
 through all of this.

832
00:33:54,280 --> 00:33:58,240
 Now, with all this repentance and grace,

833
00:33:58,240 --> 00:33:59,900
 I think there's one last question

834
00:33:59,900 --> 00:34:01,520
 that I want us to kind of wrestle with a little bit

835
00:34:01,520 --> 00:34:03,880
 before we get to a closing point.

836
00:34:03,880 --> 00:34:08,880
 See, what do you think those who were sinning,

837
00:34:08,880 --> 00:34:11,240
 those who were the sinners,

838
00:34:11,240 --> 00:34:12,460
 Jesus was having dinner with them, right?

839
00:34:12,460 --> 00:34:14,000
 What do you think they were thinking?

840
00:34:14,000 --> 00:34:18,760
 How do you think they felt when the holy teacher, Jesus,

841
00:34:18,760 --> 00:34:21,960
 talks about God welcoming sinners?

842
00:34:21,960 --> 00:34:25,800
 What do you think their feelings were in that moment?

843
00:34:25,800 --> 00:34:27,880
 Because they would be well acquainted with their sins,

844
00:34:27,880 --> 00:34:30,980
 they know where they've fallen short.

845
00:34:30,980 --> 00:34:34,940
 I wonder if when they hear that the father welcomes back,

846
00:34:34,940 --> 00:34:36,740
 kills the shattered calf,

847
00:34:36,740 --> 00:34:38,980
 puts the ring on the arm, on the finger,

848
00:34:38,980 --> 00:34:43,100
 I wonder if maybe goosebumps happened, you know?

849
00:34:43,100 --> 00:34:45,340
 I wonder if like, they might have gotten choked up

850
00:34:45,340 --> 00:34:47,560
 a little bit, maybe a lump in their throat,

851
00:34:47,560 --> 00:34:50,980
 maybe a little heavy breathing.

852
00:34:50,980 --> 00:34:54,660
 Because to know that God is going to respond

853
00:34:54,660 --> 00:34:58,400
 with such grace if we repent can be liberating.

854
00:34:58,400 --> 00:35:02,460
 It can lead us to actual repentance.

855
00:35:02,460 --> 00:35:05,500
 I think this is what Jesus is trying to show us

856
00:35:05,500 --> 00:35:07,020
 with this whole story.

857
00:35:07,020 --> 00:35:10,400
 Could it be that by learning of the father's posture

858
00:35:10,400 --> 00:35:12,300
 for restoring those who are lost,

859
00:35:12,300 --> 00:35:13,700
 some of their hearts are softened?

860
00:35:13,700 --> 00:35:15,680
 Could that be the same for us?

861
00:35:15,680 --> 00:35:18,140
 That if you ask yourself this,

862
00:35:18,140 --> 00:35:21,940
 if you could really understand

863
00:35:21,940 --> 00:35:24,500
 that no matter what it is that you've done,

864
00:35:24,500 --> 00:35:27,300
 it doesn't matter how bad it is, I mean, the worst thing,

865
00:35:27,300 --> 00:35:31,880
 if you were to have a come to your senses moment,

866
00:35:31,880 --> 00:35:34,980
 if we were just to turn,

867
00:35:34,980 --> 00:35:36,500
 remember, you don't have to have it all right yet,

868
00:35:36,500 --> 00:35:39,260
 if we were just to start that journey back home,

869
00:35:39,260 --> 00:35:41,980
 the father doesn't just say, good job,

870
00:35:41,980 --> 00:35:43,540
 thanks for not sinning anymore.

871
00:35:43,540 --> 00:35:48,500
 He rejoices, like joy, happiness, celebration,

872
00:35:48,500 --> 00:35:50,580
 let's throw a party, that's his response.

873
00:35:50,580 --> 00:35:52,860
 The scriptures would say that the angels in heaven

874
00:35:52,860 --> 00:35:54,560
 are celebrating over this.

875
00:35:54,560 --> 00:35:57,740
 I wonder if we could get that.

876
00:35:57,740 --> 00:36:01,380
 How would that impact our desire

877
00:36:01,380 --> 00:36:03,380
 or our courage to actually repent?

878
00:36:03,380 --> 00:36:08,700
 Oftentimes, repentance is seen as this doom and gloom thing,

879
00:36:08,700 --> 00:36:10,180
 but this shows us that repentance

880
00:36:10,180 --> 00:36:12,700
 is something that's met with joy.

881
00:36:12,700 --> 00:36:14,660
 We don't have to be all serious and sad when we repent.

882
00:36:14,660 --> 00:36:18,220
 We come back to God and he's excited to have us.

883
00:36:18,220 --> 00:36:20,980
 He loves us, overflowing with joy.

884
00:36:20,980 --> 00:36:23,660
 If we understand that repentance is a joyful moment,

885
00:36:23,660 --> 00:36:25,660
 would we dare repent more?

886
00:36:25,660 --> 00:36:28,460
 Could it be something that we would do regularly?

887
00:36:28,460 --> 00:36:30,220
 'Cause here's the thing, this is what Satan's trying to do.

888
00:36:30,220 --> 00:36:31,580
 Here's the big picture.

889
00:36:31,580 --> 00:36:33,340
 Go back to Genesis for a second.

890
00:36:33,340 --> 00:36:35,600
 When Adam and Eve sin in the garden,

891
00:36:35,600 --> 00:36:39,060
 they take the bite of the apple,

892
00:36:39,060 --> 00:36:41,860
 they recognize that they're naked, and what do they do?

893
00:36:41,860 --> 00:36:43,580
 They hide.

894
00:36:43,580 --> 00:36:46,380
 They distance themselves.

895
00:36:46,380 --> 00:36:49,200
 They separate, sin separates us from God,

896
00:36:49,200 --> 00:36:51,420
 but this is what grace does.

897
00:36:51,420 --> 00:36:53,620
 Grace says that if you would come to your senses,

898
00:36:53,620 --> 00:36:55,420
 if you would put your faith in Jesus,

899
00:36:55,420 --> 00:36:57,180
 if you would understand that he is the way,

900
00:36:57,180 --> 00:36:58,100
 the truth, and the life,

901
00:36:58,100 --> 00:37:01,580
 if you would just make an effort to come towards him,

902
00:37:01,580 --> 00:37:03,260
 you don't have to get it all right,

903
00:37:03,260 --> 00:37:06,560
 but if you would just take a step, he'll meet you.

904
00:37:06,560 --> 00:37:11,580
 He'll sprint towards you, and he will be so glad,

905
00:37:11,580 --> 00:37:12,620
 not just to forgive,

906
00:37:12,620 --> 00:37:15,900
 but to make you a part of the family again,

907
00:37:15,900 --> 00:37:19,720
 to make you an heir, someone who gets things from him,

908
00:37:19,720 --> 00:37:21,000
 someone who is loved by him,

909
00:37:21,000 --> 00:37:24,400
 someone who is protected by him, taken care of by him.

910
00:37:24,400 --> 00:37:29,040
 Guys, I pray this is something that we can understand

911
00:37:29,040 --> 00:37:29,880
 and fully get.

912
00:37:29,880 --> 00:37:32,480
 I pray that the courage needed

913
00:37:32,480 --> 00:37:36,900
 from an understanding of the extreme grace of the Father

914
00:37:36,900 --> 00:37:38,720
 would find its way to you,

915
00:37:38,720 --> 00:37:41,600
 because repentance is a bit of an invitation.

916
00:37:42,620 --> 00:37:46,040
 It's God making it clear that you're welcomed back

917
00:37:46,040 --> 00:37:47,760
 and you're wanted back.

918
00:37:47,760 --> 00:37:49,280
 So I think we all need to keep this in mind.

919
00:37:49,280 --> 00:37:50,640
 You're wanted.

920
00:37:50,640 --> 00:37:52,000
 God wants you in his family.

921
00:37:52,000 --> 00:37:54,320
 If he didn't, he would just forgive you

922
00:37:54,320 --> 00:37:55,600
 and let you on your way.

923
00:37:55,600 --> 00:37:58,120
 But he wants you to be a part of that family.

924
00:37:58,120 --> 00:37:59,960
 He wants you to be under that covering,

925
00:37:59,960 --> 00:38:01,240
 under that protection.

926
00:38:01,240 --> 00:38:04,960
 He desires to see you not just forgiven of your sin.

927
00:38:04,960 --> 00:38:09,000
 John 3:16, "For God so hated sin

928
00:38:09,000 --> 00:38:09,840
 "that he came into the world."

929
00:38:09,840 --> 00:38:11,720
 No, for God so loved the world.

930
00:38:11,720 --> 00:38:14,260
 His posture is love towards you.

931
00:38:14,260 --> 00:38:17,580
 He desires to see you flourish, to see you at peace,

932
00:38:17,580 --> 00:38:21,260
 to see you the way that he's intended your life to be.

933
00:38:21,260 --> 00:38:27,540
 And that takes place when we're able to turn from our sins.

934
00:38:27,540 --> 00:38:29,100
 Here, I wanna leave us with this.

935
00:38:29,100 --> 00:38:30,580
 As the worship team makes their way up,

936
00:38:30,580 --> 00:38:34,260
 there is one of my favorite C.S. Lewis quotes.

937
00:38:34,260 --> 00:38:35,780
 And if you don't know who C.S. Lewis is,

938
00:38:35,780 --> 00:38:37,060
 the 90th series is incredible.

939
00:38:37,060 --> 00:38:38,020
 Please read it.

940
00:38:38,020 --> 00:38:39,820
 It'll enrich your life.

941
00:38:39,840 --> 00:38:43,560
 But Lewis, in one of his books called "The Screwtape Letters,"

942
00:38:43,560 --> 00:38:48,120
 which is a book where demons are writing letters

943
00:38:48,120 --> 00:38:50,000
 to Satan about people.

944
00:38:50,000 --> 00:38:53,220
 Very wild, very crazy, but very insightful.

945
00:38:53,220 --> 00:38:57,360
 This one demon is writing.

946
00:38:57,360 --> 00:39:02,360
 And he says this about the human effort,

947
00:39:02,360 --> 00:39:07,600
 about the divine satisfaction and love.

948
00:39:07,600 --> 00:39:09,760
 And it is profound and it blows my mind.

949
00:39:09,760 --> 00:39:10,800
 And it stays with me.

950
00:39:10,800 --> 00:39:11,800
 I've written songs about it.

951
00:39:11,800 --> 00:39:13,360
 I've talked about it like all the time.

952
00:39:13,360 --> 00:39:14,940
 I wanna leave you guys with it

953
00:39:14,940 --> 00:39:16,000
 'cause I hope it can help you.

954
00:39:16,000 --> 00:39:19,760
 It says this, "He," meaning the father,

955
00:39:19,760 --> 00:39:22,240
 "He wants them," meaning us,

956
00:39:22,240 --> 00:39:26,000
 "He wants them to learn how to walk

957
00:39:26,000 --> 00:39:30,720
 "and must therefore take away his hands.

958
00:39:30,720 --> 00:39:37,100
 "And if only the will to walk is really there,

959
00:39:38,920 --> 00:39:43,920
 "he is pleased," get this, "even in their stumbles."

960
00:39:43,920 --> 00:39:49,680
 Guys, for lots of us, it won't be a clean walk home.

961
00:39:49,680 --> 00:39:52,280
 For lots of us, it will be stumbles.

962
00:39:52,280 --> 00:39:55,700
 It's not an easy route back,

963
00:39:55,700 --> 00:39:58,460
 but here's the thing, the heavy lifting is done by him.

964
00:39:58,460 --> 00:40:01,560
 He's gonna carry you through.

965
00:40:01,560 --> 00:40:03,780
 He's your strength.

966
00:40:03,780 --> 00:40:05,800
 He is a rock that you build your hope on.

967
00:40:05,800 --> 00:40:07,240
 He is your strong tower.

968
00:40:07,240 --> 00:40:10,440
 He is your ever-present help in times of need

969
00:40:10,440 --> 00:40:13,040
 and in times where you don't realize that you have need.

970
00:40:13,040 --> 00:40:18,400
 Even in our stumbles, he will be pleased

971
00:40:18,400 --> 00:40:19,600
 and he will be with us.

972
00:40:19,600 --> 00:40:22,540
 So God, we come to you this morning

973
00:40:22,540 --> 00:40:27,540
 and we recognize and are overwhelmed by your grace,

974
00:40:27,540 --> 00:40:32,180
 by your extreme fervent love,

975
00:40:32,180 --> 00:40:37,180
 by love so extreme that it welcomes in the center.

976
00:40:37,740 --> 00:40:40,740
 It welcomes in those of us who are Christians

977
00:40:40,740 --> 00:40:42,180
 and who have made such terrible mistakes

978
00:40:42,180 --> 00:40:44,460
 that we're afraid to come to you.

979
00:40:44,460 --> 00:40:48,100
 It welcomes, it dines with, it reinstates,

980
00:40:48,100 --> 00:40:49,580
 and it restores us.

981
00:40:49,580 --> 00:40:53,160
 So Holy Spirit, there are so many lies

982
00:40:53,160 --> 00:40:56,160
 and so many fears about being judged by God,

983
00:40:56,160 --> 00:40:59,240
 but to the one who would return,

984
00:40:59,240 --> 00:41:05,900
 there is this truth that your love should cast out our fear,

985
00:41:06,980 --> 00:41:09,140
 that your love is enough,

986
00:41:09,140 --> 00:41:12,280
 that the blood of Jesus runs deeper

987
00:41:12,280 --> 00:41:14,740
 than anything your child or children could do.

988
00:41:14,740 --> 00:41:18,280
 And so God, help us not just believe it,

989
00:41:18,280 --> 00:41:22,620
 but Holy Spirit, would you put that as a seed into our heart

990
00:41:22,620 --> 00:41:26,060
 and would you keep that soil fertile so this grows in us

991
00:41:26,060 --> 00:41:30,100
 into a tree of understanding that you want us

992
00:41:30,100 --> 00:41:32,180
 and you welcome us.

993
00:41:32,180 --> 00:41:34,300
 And no matter what we've done,

994
00:41:34,300 --> 00:41:37,200
 if the thief on the cross could get in at the last minute,

995
00:41:37,200 --> 00:41:39,500
 it doesn't matter what we've done,

996
00:41:39,500 --> 00:41:40,800
 if we would turn to you,

997
00:41:40,800 --> 00:41:44,540
 we will find hope,

998
00:41:44,540 --> 00:41:47,620
 we will find a father who isn't waiting to beat us,

999
00:41:47,620 --> 00:41:48,900
 but who is overjoyed.

1000
00:41:48,900 --> 00:41:52,060
 God, for those of us who feel distant,

1001
00:41:52,060 --> 00:41:53,260
 who feel like we can't talk to you

1002
00:41:53,260 --> 00:41:55,340
 'cause our sin is so bad,

1003
00:41:55,340 --> 00:41:56,360
 I rebuke that lie.

1004
00:41:56,360 --> 00:42:00,480
 Holy Spirit, would you come in and speak your truth?

1005
00:42:00,480 --> 00:42:03,700
 Would you remind that light shines best in darkness,

1006
00:42:03,700 --> 00:42:06,060
 that you came not to be served,

1007
00:42:06,060 --> 00:42:09,980
 but to serve us, that those of us who were sick,

1008
00:42:09,980 --> 00:42:11,880
 those of us who were in need of you,

1009
00:42:11,880 --> 00:42:14,580
 that's who you came for.

1010
00:42:14,580 --> 00:42:18,860
 Lord, would you open our hearts,

1011
00:42:18,860 --> 00:42:22,540
 lead us to that coming to our senses moment

1012
00:42:22,540 --> 00:42:26,380
 and give us the courage to turn our hearts,

1013
00:42:26,380 --> 00:42:30,000
 our minds, our postures and our will back to you.

1014
00:42:30,000 --> 00:42:32,740
 In Jesus' name, amen.

